RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 69. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AZTEC LEGEND bumped mildly with the horse to his inside leaving the gate, recovered to lead the field on the inside up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the turn and kicked clear in the lane. CRUISING DEREK veered out and bumped with the horse to his outside at the start, chased the leaders up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the two and three path and kept on to the finish. AWESOME PRINCE trailed the field on the outside early, began to move up racing in the four and five path around the bend and continued to improve position in the stretch. RUSTY PISTOL pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the turn, weakened in the lane and was later vanned off. SMART DRESSER bumped with the horse to his inside leaving the gate, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two path and showed no kick. FAST FIXER bumped with the horses to both sides at the break, raced in the middle of the pack between horses for the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the turn and faded in the lane. ATLANTIC VAQUERO hit the gate leaving it, raced off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the bend from the four path and was empty in the stretch. THE RIDER OF HORSE TWO, CRUISING DEREK, FILED AN OBJECTION AGAINST HORSE ONE, AZTEC LEGEND, CITING INTERFERENCE AT THE START. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

ROOKIE SALSA dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the turn and in upper stretch, was caught in the final furlong and chased the winner home from there. OLD TIME REVIVAL dueled on the inside through the opening half mile, continued to battle in upper stretch and gave way late. LAUDERDALE bumped lightly with the horse to his inside leaving the gate, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and made no bid. EL SOLITARIO bumped with the horse to his outside at the break, trailed the field through the early going, saved ground around the turn and was never a factor. CHILL HAZE chased the leaders up the backstretch, began to drop back while racing in the two path around the turn and tired further in the lane.

DUDESFIRSTDARLING pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn and chased the winner home in the lane. LUNA AMARILLA chased the leaders through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the turn and kept on to the finish. GINGER SPARKLE veered out leaving the gate, trailed the field up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn and improved position mildly in the stretch while never threatening. UNKOALAFIED bumped with the horse to her inside and was pinched back leaving the gate, raced off the pace up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and was empty in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 4 1M Turf CR: 67. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $16,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Th an $16,000 And Since Then Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $16,000 Or More.). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIGEIA raced in the two path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the three path, began a bid passing the quarter pole, gained ground outside in upper stretch and pulled clear. IRISH KITTEN raced in the three path around the first turn, stalked the pace setters on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the second bend, dueled in the lane and chased the winner home late. NEWYEARSPRESENT tracked the leader on the outside through the opening half mile, began a bid from the two path coming around the turn, dueled in upper stretch, was caught by the winner in the final furlong and kept on to the finish. SHE IS ROYALTY raced in the four path early, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the four path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and improved position in the lane. SYLLABUS raced at the back of the pack on the inside through the opening half mile, navigated the far turn from the two path and improved position in the stretch. I'LL GO ALL IN saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, was forced to steady near the three eighths pole when BYZANTINE EMPIRE backed up into him, switched out the three path and flattened out in the lane. LIFENHOWULIVIT raced in the two path early, continued up the backstretch at the back of the pack on the outside, angled in to save ground around the second bend and never threatened. BYZANTINE EMPIRE led the field while saving ground around the first turn, continued to show the way while racing up the backstretch, began to drop back from the rail coming around the far turn and tired further in the stretch. BLACK KARMA raced in the middle of the pack on the inside around the first turn and up the backstretch, navigated the far bend from the two path and faded in the lane. GET IT trailed the field the entire way around the oval, saved ground throughout and was never a factor. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE FAR TURN. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 6 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since January 24 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since December 24 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHIMMERING LIGHT raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the second turn and in upper stretch and held off a closer at the wire. MAPACHE G raced in the two path around the first turn, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, began to move up from the four path coming around the second bend and continued to gain ground late. WATCH FOR THE LUTE hit the gate leaving it, recovered to lead the field while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the far bend and dug in the lane, giving way late. PAPA JIMMY shied away from an alligator but was held firmly in place in the three and four path by his rider headed around the first turn, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the three path and finished evenly. MACHO REAL bobbled slightly leaving the gate, saved ground around the first turn, trailed well behind the field up the backstretch, came around the far bend in the two path and improved position mildly while never threatening. ACTION WARRIOR tracked the pace setters on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the far turn and faded further in the lane. NIP OF BOURBON saved ground around the first turn, raced into traffic and steadied slightly entering the backstretch, continued in the middle of the pack from there, raced in the two path around the second turn and was empty in the stretch. THE TRAINER OF HORSE TWO, NIP OF BOURBON, FILED AN OBJECTION AGAINST HORSE FOUR, SHIMMERING LIGHT, CITING INTERFERENCE COMING OFF THE FIRST TURN. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH. AN ALLIGATOR WAS ON THE TRACK AT THE START OF THE BACKSTRETCH AND MAY HAVE CAUSED OFF CAMERA INTERFERENCE WITH SOME OF THE HORSES IN THE FIELD.
